&quot; f.write(result) where “test_data” is the *.csv for test set, e.g. data-fully-aug/test/together.txt.csv; while the “nbest_path” is the final file generated by step 2. step 4. Change the &quot;trainer.py&quot; to output the scoreDuring evluation, we need to save the CTC loss as wav2vec2 score. 123456if all_losses is not None: save_losses = np.array(all_losses) print(save_losses.shape) print(save_losses) np.savetxt('/project_bdda7/bdda/sjhu/Projects/wav2vec2/ua/nbest_data/w2v_score.txt', save_losses, delimiter=',') metrics[f&quot;{metric_key_prefix}_loss&quot;] = all_losses.mean().item() step 5. Change the training codesince we need to forward the data and evaluate, we could make the training data contain one item and the learning rate as 0 to make the model freeze; also the training epoch is 1, eval step is 1 and per_device_eval_batch_size=1.please ref the file “/project_bdda7/bdda/sjhu/Projects/wav2vec2/xlsr/JCCOCC_MoCA/run_wav2vec2_get_nbest_score.py” step 6. Combine the resultsAfter get the score, we need to add the utt_id. Since we do not shuffle, we could merge as the following: 1awk '{print $1}' words.txt | paste -d' ' - w2v_score.txt &gt; nbest30_w2v_score.txt Now, we have the both tdnn-f score and wav2vec2 score. By linear interpolation, we can get the final score. 12python3 /project_bdda7/bdda/sjhu/Projects/wav2vec2/xlsr/JCCOCC_MoCA/scripts/get_w2v_tdnn_score_and_sort.py nbest_data/test/nbest30_w2v_score.txt nbest_data/test/30best_acscore_lmscore_final_word ${tdnn_weight} ${w2v_weight} nbest_data/test/final_results/ nbest_data/test/ans &gt;&gt; w2v_tdnn_lhuc_combination_results_test
